{
  "texts": [
    "Supervised learning algorithms are the most used in policy development problems.",
    "They are used as training data examples of input vectors along with their corresponding target variables.",
    "Their aim is to predict some target variables.",
    "When the training data examples consist of input vectors without corresponding targets, the problem is an unsupervised one.",
    "The aim in such a problem is to match the input data to similar groups (i.e., clustering problem) or to determine the distribution that generates the input data."
  ]
}